snippet.textDisplay: Uhhh.....why does the Big Dipper being in the nights sky mean it has to be in the Southern Hemisphere? The Big Dipper will be visible from different parts of the northern and Southern Hemispheres throughout different times of the year as earth rotates around the sun AND its axis. For example, I can go outside tonight, March in the northern hemisphere, and see the Big Dipper. However, give it another 3-4 months I will not be able to see the Big Dipper and more of the Southern Hemisphere will be. So, unless you have an exact “date” of when that windwaker image is taken in game, there’s no way to be certain what hemisphere you are in
snippet.textOriginal: Uhhh.....why does the Big Dipper being in the nights sky mean it has to be in the Southern Hemisphere?
